data.responses: {"Q0":"I can make a mental picture and keep it in my memory."}

{"Q0":"I'm tired this morning. This time I tried to remember one museum. Sometimes the other words came to me after that. Had a hard time today remembering, sorry. And I totally forgot that one word at the beginning. Bad day."}
{"Q0":"I aim on the 3 words per specific room and try to make a story"}

{"Q0":"Different strategy today!  I looked at all the words and then repeated and remembered the words from the first box and the second box.  While I repeated those words I looked at the third box.  I kept repeating them when I did the \"distraction\" task.  Then filled in from my repeated list and chose the others that I remembered!!!!!"}
{"Q0":"Pretty fun!  I think you are generous in your compensation!  Thanks!"}
{"Q0":"Typically I tried to remember the top left box of items. I also would try to relate words to things."}
{"Q0":"Same as yesterday, trying to remember 6 of the 9 and whatever I can of the rest."}
{"Q0":"I tried to remember all the words in groups."}

{"Q0":"I tried to say it in my head and out loud. If it was an easy group, like insects, I would try to memorize it first.\n\nI took the room first, then tried to memorize the words, and then go on to another room."}
{"Q0":"My memory isn't great, but I found this study to be fun and interesting. Thanks for the great payments throughout this study."}
{"Q0":"I tried to remember the place of some words that stuck out to me and then tried to make a connection between the other words in the room with that word."}
{"Q0":"I tried to \"rap\" them to myself and use visual memory too"}
{"Q0":"Thank you so much for your generosity and letting me do this for you, really enjoyed this hit set!"}
{"Q0":"I repeated the groups of words outloud. I focused on remembering the words from two chambers. It was easier when the words were presented one chamber at a time. "}
{"Q0":"Very stressful. Thank you for the opportunity."}
{"Q0":"i tried say the words in a rhyme/song like manner....it started working well but then i lost the rhythm and started doing poorly,i went  back to trying to remember one room fully"}

{"Q0":"I tried to remember the same six pots each round and then glance at the other free places.  When there was a theme to each room I was able to use deduction.  Otherwise I went with mt intuition."}
{"Q0":"I tried to make a story up with the words and remember what box it was in."}
{"Q0":"I tried to remember just a couple of rooms. I looked as the words in each room belonged together.  I tried to say each word out loud to remind myself."}
{"Q0":"I thought I did better as I went along. "}
{"Q0":"I looked at groups and could remember.  If words were just random, I visualized position of words."}
{"Q0":"I have really enjoyed this study!   I hope you put more together!"}
{"Q0":"I remembered the first one in each then when they had similarities then guessed"}
{"Q0":"This time I was able to say at laud 4 first words - from left upper corner and then observe the rest of them and try to remember."}
{"Q0":"great survey, would love to see more !"}
{"Q0":"i put the words together in a list from the first rows, kind of glanced at the order of the last words"}

{"Q0":"I was so busy trying to remember the words that I forgot the word to remember in the beginning!!\nI just tried to memorize at least two of the boxes, either with just memory or a word or sentence that I made up."}
{"Q0":"Really fun!! Hope you do more of these!"}
{"Q0":"I tried to group the words together. Sometimes by room, sometimes by the groups of words"}
{"Q0":"Whole scene but divided by room. Memorized the first letter of each word in a sequence. For words with the same starting letter I said them out loud to myself"}
{"Q0":"Related groups were easier to remember for sure!"}

{"Q0":"I use the first letter from every word to tried and remember those I thought it would be easier. It didn't end up getting any easier but I did manage to get a couple of 9/9 today but I knew six of the words and I guess that the last three and I got them."}
{"Q0":"good study great pay keep me in the contact list please AP4A0MZOKR52J"}
{"Q0":"Abbreviating in my head, using acronyms, making up rhymes. I did not lump words together."}
{"Q0":"It was easier when the words were related, then I tried to group them. If they weren't related then I would work downard from the top, and then remember the last word of the last room."}
{"Q0":"I did not have any specific strategies, I just tried my best to remember"}
{"Q0":"I grouped the words in the same rooms, then tried to memorize them. In some tasks, the words were related to each other."}
